g.text: The indicator located in the lower
left middle of the unit and has three
states that you need to be aware of.
Solid Green: Indicates that the
internal battery needs to be replaced. This
is something that we can do ourselves.
Flashing Green: Indicates that a problem
has been detected. The unit is safe to use,
but the gas company should be called to
inspect the unit.
Solid Red is the most important. Stop using
the unit immediately and call to have the
gas company service the unit.
Important Indicator Lamp
The gas control lever at
